{{POV|date=September 2012}} {{Infobox publisher | image = | parent = Ascend Learning<ref name=ascend>{{cite web|title=Jones & Bartlett Learning|url=http://www.ascendlearning.com/companies/jb-learning/|website=Ascend Learning|accessdate=1 January 2015}}</ref> | status = | founded = {{Start date|1983}}<ref name=jbOverview>{{cite web|title=Company Overview|website=Jones & Barlett Learning|url=http://www.jblearning.com/about/overview/|accessdate=20 March 2015}}</ref> | founder = {{unbulleted list | Donald W. Jones | Arthur Bartlett<ref name=jbOverview/> }} | successor = | country = [[United States]] | headquarters = [[Burlington, Massachusetts]]<ref name=jbOverview/> | distribution = | publications = [[Book]]s | topics = Educational & Professional Publishing | imprints = {{unbulleted list | Informed (quick reference) | Tarascon (medical)<ref name=brands>{{cite web|title=Our Brands|url=http://www.jblearning.com/brandspartners/brands/|website=Jones & Bartlett Learning|accessdate=20 March 2015}}</ref> }} | revenue = {{USD|84}} million (2007)<ref>{{cite web|title=Industry ranking|url=http://www.jbpub.com/company/industryrank.cfm|website=Jones and Bartlett|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20070502193503/http://www.jbpub.com/company/industryRank.cfm|archivedate=2 May 2007}}</ref> | numemployees = | nasdaq = | url = {{URL|http://www.jblearning.com|jblearning.com}} }}
'''Jones & Bartlett Learning''', a division of Ascend Learning,<ref name=ascend/> is a provider of instructional, assessment and learning-performance management solutions for the secondary, post-secondary, and professional markets. The name comes from Donald W. Jones, the company's founder, and Arthur Bartlett, the first editor.{{Citation needed|date=March 2015}}
==History== Founded by Donald W. Jones and Arthur Bartlett in 1983, the original editorial office was located in [[Woods Hole, Massachusetts]],<ref name=jbOverview/> and the company's corporate logo is the local [[Nobska lighthouse]].{{Citation needed|date=March 2015}} In 1986, Jones and Bartlett acquired the Wadsworth Health Sciences publishing program from [[The Thomson Corporation]], which moved the company into nursing and health sciences.{{Citation needed|date=March 2015}}
In 1988, the company was named by ''New England Business Magazine'' as one of the 100 fastest-growing companies in New England.{{Citation needed|date=July 2008}} In 1989, they opened their first office in [[London]]. In 1993, they opened an office in [[Singapore]], and an office in [[Toronto]] in 1994.{{Citation needed|date=March 2015}} Their corporate headquarters moved to [[Sudbury, Massachusetts]] in 1995.<ref name=expansion2011>{{cite web|title=Jones & Bartlett Learning expands into new office space in Burlington|url=http://www.jblearning.com/about/newspress/content/pressreleasecontent/298/|website=Jones & Bartlett Learning|accessdate=20 March 2015|date=12 July 2011}}</ref> In 2011, Jones & Bartlett Learning moved its offices in Sudbury and [[Maynard, Massachusetts]] to Burlington, Massachusetts, sharing a building with other Ascend Learning corporate offices.<ref name=expansion2011/>
